where \( \vec A \) may be a nonlinear function of \( \vec x \). For example, if we think of Poisson&amp;rsquo;s equation in 1D,
&lt;span&gt;
 \[\dv{^2 \phi}{x^2} = - \rho_c\]
&lt;/span&gt;

and apply finite differencing,
&lt;span&gt;
